    public interface ITagValueIteratorBindable<I extends Iterator<ITagValue>>
extends IBindable<I>
    Interface to be implemented by all ITagValue collections capable of providing iteration with reusable java.util.Iterators.

    No iterators returned here are capable of modifying the structure of the underlying ITagValue collection. Consequently, the following operations are not supported:

    • java.util.ListIterator#remove()
    • java.util.ListIterator#add()
    • java.util.ListIterator#set()

    Calling any of them results in an UnsupportedOperationException.

    • Method Detail

      • bind

        I bind(I iterator,
       ITagValue returnValueBuffer)
        Bind an iterator to a collection of ITagValues.

        This method binds the specified iterator to the collection of ITagValues and resets it to the start so that iteration is over the complete collection. If an attempt is made to pass an incompatible iterator type a ClassCastException is thrown. It is possible to check beforehand using the IBindable.isBindable(Object) method.

        The caller may specify the return value buffer. This is like to be very efficient and is guaranteed not to involve object creation. However, modifying the ITagValue entry during iteration has no effect.

        If no return value buffer is specified then modifying the ITagValue entry modifies the underlying data, however, there are no guarantees about object creation.

        Parameters:
        iterator - The iterator to bind to this collection. May be null, in which case a new iterator is created which is suitable for subsequent reuse.
        returnValueBuffer - The buffer via which to return ITagValue entries. May be null in which cases the implementation chooses the most efficient return buffer. If supplied then modifying the returned ITagValue entries has no effect.
        Returns:
        Iterator over ITagValues using the supplied buffer to refer to each underlying element. The supplied iterator (provided it was not null) initialized to the start of the collection.
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - If the supplied iterator is the wrong type for this collection.

      • bind

        I bind(I iterator,
       int tag,
       ITagValue returnValueBuffer)
        Bind an iterator to a collection of ITagValues.

        This method has precisely the same semantics as bind(Iterator, ITagValue), except that iteration commences at the first instance of a ITagValue which contains the specified tag (if any).

        Parameters:
        iterator - The iterator to bind to this collection. May be null, in which case a new iterator is created which is suitable for subsequent reuse.
        tag - The tag at which to start iteration. A tag ≤ 0 is considered out of range and implies the start of the collection. If multiple instances of this tag exist iteration commences at the first one.
        returnValueBuffer - The buffer via which to return ITagValue entries. May be null in which cases the implementation chooses the most efficient return buffer. If supplied then modifying the returned ITagValue entries has no effect.
        Returns:
        Iterator over ITagValues using the supplied buffer to refer to each underlying element. The supplied iterator (provided it was not null) initialized to the start of the collection.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - If no ITagValue exists with the specified tag.
        ClassCastException - If the supplied iterator is the wrong type for this collection.
